text: Isn't it strange how movies nowadays can't seem to be interesting or even sell tickets without being morally debased? If this is really the low that America must sink to to entertain a group of perverts, it truly is a depressing sight. And if me, a 15 year old boy, who should be glorifying sex by the media's stereotypical view of teenagers can see this. Why can't anyone else seem to? THE TITLE OF THE MOVIE IS EUPHEMISM FOR A PORNOGRAPHY FILM! And it's not a good one either. I'm honestly disgusted by this and we as a society should be too. This is nothing but an insult to intelligence and only plays on males sex drive. Which by the way, makes us make dumb decisions in the first place. Almost as dumb of a decision as whomever decided this should be a plot for a movie! If we ever want to make a move towards a more civilized and complex society where people can be happy and productive, we need to do away with such debased filth. All this is a lie. Sex is not like this. This is not what sex is about everyone. But we seem to have forgotten that through our glorification of pornography. Also don't think that I'm writing this essay on morals because I'm some church hopping bible jockey, I'm writing this in pure shock that such a premise for a film could actually be released and advertised. They try to cover it up with jokes and even heavy drug use! Seriously cocaine use? I'm done. Just done. If this is really what we call entertainment, I'll be in my pillow fort watching Tom and Jerry in my pajamas. Alone. Not snorting crack, or making a "Sex Tape". Fuck this.
